import React from 'react';
import professorPhoto from './professorPhoto.jpeg';
const HomePage = () => {
  return (
    <div className="container mx-auto px-4">
      <header className="bg-blue-800 text-white text-center p-6">
      <img src={professorPhoto} alt="Ramalingam Sridhar" className="mx-auto rounded-full w-32 h-32 object-cover" />
        <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold">Ramalingam Sridhar</h1>
        <p className="text-xl">Associate Professor, Department of Computer Science and Engineering</p>
        <p className="mt-2">University at Buffalo, The State University of New York</p>
      </header>

      <nav className="flex justify-center space-x-4 bg-gray-200 p-4">
        {['Bio', 'Research/HPVSA Lab', 'Teaching', 'Publications', 'Professional Activities', 'News', 'Resource Links'].map((item) => (
          <a href={`#${item.toLowerCase()}`} className="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">{item}</a>
        ))}
      </nav>

      <main>
      <section id="bio" className="my-8">
  <h2 className="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Bio</h2>
  <p><strong>Professor Ramalingam Sridhar</strong> is an esteemed Associate Professor at the University of Buffalo's Department of Computer Science and Engineering, renowned for his pioneering contributions to green computing and energy-aware systems. With a career dedicated to advancing the field of computer science, Professor Sridhar's research has been instrumental in shaping the future of energy-efficient technology and sustainable computing practices.</p>

  <p><strong>Research Focus:</strong> At the heart of Professor Sridhar's academic pursuit is a profound commitment to exploring the frontiers of Green Computing, Energy-aware Mobile Systems, and the Internet of Things. His work delves into the critical aspects of Hardware, Systems and Security, VLSI Circuits and Systems, Wireless Networks and Security, Embedded Technologies, and Computer Architecture. Through his research, Professor Sridhar aims to unveil innovative solutions that mitigate environmental impacts and foster the development of energy-efficient technologies.</p>

  <p>From <strong>January 2003 to December 2004</strong>, Professor Sridhar served as a Distinguished Lecturer for the IEEE Circuits and Systems Society, a role through which he shared his vast knowledge and insights with the global academic community. His influence extends into the realm of scholarly publications, having held editorship positions in prestigious journals such as the IEEE Transactions on VLSI Systems and the International Journal of Computers and Their Applications.</p>

  <p><strong>Professional Engagement:</strong> Professor Sridhar's professional activities highlight his leadership and commitment to the scientific community. He has played pivotal roles in numerous conferences and symposiums, including serving as the Steering Committee Chair for SoCC 2013 and the General Chair for SoCC 2012. His dedication to fostering academic excellence and innovation is further evidenced by his involvement in the program committees of significant conferences like MobiHoc 2006 and WowMom 2006.</p>

  <p>As a <strong>Member</strong> of the IEEE CAS Society Technical Committee on VLSI Systems and Applications, among others, Professor Sridhar contributes to advancing knowledge in communications, nanotechnologies, multimedia systems, and neural networks. His tenure as the past chair of the VLSI Systems and Applications TC underscores his leadership and influence in the field.</p>

  <p>Professor Ramalingam Sridhar's illustrious career is a testament to his enduring passion and unwavering dedication to enriching the scientific and academic landscapes. His visionary research and contributions continue to inspire students, colleagues, and the broader community, paving the way for a more sustainable and technologically advanced future.</p>
</section>


        {/* Repeat for other sections */}
      </main>

     {/* Add more vertical space above the footer, if needed */}
<footer className="mt-10 bg-gray-800 text-white text-center p-6">
  Contact info and other details here...
</footer>

    </div>
  );
};

export default HomePage;
